mm: fix use-after-free in slab allocator

A race condition in the slab allocator can lead to use-after-free
when kmem_cache_free() is called concurrently with cache shrinking.

The issue is that the object is returned to the per-cpu list before
the page reference count is updated, allowing another CPU to reclaim
the page while the object is still in use.

Fix by updating the page reference count before adding the object
to the per-cpu list.

Fixes: abc123 ("mm: optimize slab allocation path")
